text: Manchester Township is a civil township of Washtenaw County in the U.S. state of Michigan. 4,626 people lived here at the 2020 census. The Village of Manchester is located within the township. According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 38.76 square miles (100.39 km2), of which 37.86 square miles (98.06 km2) is land and 0.90 square miles (2.33 km2) (2.32%) is water. ==References== Category:Townships in Michigan
title: Manchester Township, Michigan
